picture.
"I
soon
left
Mr.
and
Mrs.
Crimsworth
to
themselves;
a
servant
conducted
me
to
my
bed
room;
in
closing
my
chamber
door,
I
shut
out
all
intruders
you,
Charles,
as
well
as
the
rest.
"Good
bye
for
the
present,
"WILLIAM
CRIMSWORTH."
To
this
letter
I
never
got
an
answer;
before
my
old
friend
received
it,
he
had
accepted
a
Government
appointment
in
one
of
the
colonies,
and
was
already
on
his
way
to
the
scene
of
his
official
labours.
What
has
become
of
him
since,
I
know
not.
The
leisure
time
I
have
at
command,
and
which
I
intended
to
employ
for
his
private
