out.
Mr.
Crimsworth
stirred
the
fire,
then
folded
his
arms,
and
sat
a
moment
thinking,
his
lips
compressed,
his
brow
knit.
I
had
nothing
to
do
but
to
watch
him
how
well
his
features
were
cut!
what
a
handsome
man
he
was!
Whence,
then,
came
that
air
of
contraction
that
narrow
and
hard
