since
you
know
French
and
German,
I
will
take
you
as
second
clerk
to
manage
the
foreign
correspondence
of
the
house.
I
shall
give
you
a
good
salary
90l.
a
year
and
now,"
he
continued,
raising
his
voice,
"hear
once
for
all
what
I
have
to
say
about
our
relationship,
and
all
that
sort
of
humbug!
I
must
have
no
nonsense
on
that
point;
it
would
never
suit
me.
I
shall
excuse
you
nothing
on
the
plea
of
being
my
brother;
if
I
find
you
stupid,
negligent,
dissipated,
idle,
or
possessed
