I
wrote.
I
thought
he
was
trying
to
read
my
character,
but
I
felt
as
secure
against
his
scrutiny
as
if
I
had
had
on
a
casque
with
the
visor
down
or
rather
I
showed
him
my
countenance
with
the
confidence
that
one
would
show
an
unlearned
man
a
letter
written
in
Greek;
he
might
see
lines,
and
trace
characters,
but
he
could
make
nothing
of
them;
my
nature
was
not
his
nature,
and
its
signs
were
to
