I
remember
many
called
me
miser
at
the
time,
and
I
used
to
couple
the
reproach
with
this
consolation
better
to
be
misunderstood
now
than
repulsed
hereafter.
At
this
day
I
had
my
reward;
I
had
had
it
before,
when
on
parting
with
my
irritated
uncles
one
