Tim
was
"a
religious
man"
himself;
indeed,
he
was
"a
joined
Methodist,"
which
did
not
(be
it
understood)
prevent
him
from
being
at
the
same
time
an
engrained
rascal,
and
he
came
away
much
posed
at
hearing
this
account
of
my
piety.
Having
imparted
it
to
Mr.
Crimsworth,
that
