"Your
bread
was
dirty,
man!"
cried
Hunsden
"dirty
and
unwholesome!
It
came
through
the
hands
of
a
tyrant,
for
I
tell
you
Crimsworth
is
a
tyrant,
a
tyrant
to
his
workpeople,
a
tyrant
to
his
clerks,
and
will
some
