"That
will
just
suit
me,"
said
I.
"Well,
and
where's
your
gratitude?"
demanded
Mr.
Hunsden;
"don't
you
know
how
to
say
'Thank
you?'"
"I've
fifteen
pounds
and
a
watch,
which
my
godmother,
whom
I
never
saw,
gave
me
eighteen
years
ago,"
was
my
rather
irrelevant
