"Merci,
merci,
madame
au
revoir."
And
I
backed
at
last
out
of
the
apartment.
Having
regained
my
own
room,
I
set
myself
to
turn
over
in
my
mind
the
incident
of
the
evening.
It
seemed
a
queer
affair
altogether,
and
queerly
managed;
the
two
old
women
had
made
quite
a
little
intricate
mess
of
it;
still
I
found
that
the
uppermost
feeling
in
my
mind
on
the
subject
was
one
of
satisfaction.
In
the
first
place
it
would
be
a
change
to
give
lessons
in
another
seminary,
and
then
to
teach
young
ladies
would
be
an
occupation
so
interesting
to
be
admitted
at
all
into
a
ladies'
boarding
school
would
be
an
incident
so
new
in
my
life.
Besides,
thought
I,
as
I
