for
something
smarter.
At
last
I
concluded
it
would
be
a
waste
of
labour.
"Doubtless,"
thought
I,
"she
is
some
stiff
old
maid;
for
though
the
daughter
of
Madame
Reuter,
she
may
well
number
upwards
of
forty
