on
that
school
boy,
Crimsworth;
he
has
presumed
to
fall
in
love,
which
he
dared
not
have
done
unless
you
had
given
him
room
to
hope."
"What
do
you
say,
Francois?
Do
you
say
Crimsworth
is
in
love
with
me?"
"Over
head
and
ears."
"Has
he
told
you
so?"
"No
but
I
see
it
in
his
face:
he
blushes
whenever
your
name
is
mentioned."
A
