yet
such
as
it
was,
I
had
hitherto
seen
nothing
like
it
in
the
course
of
my
professorial
experience.
The
girl's
mind
had
conceived
a
picture
of
the
hut,
of
the
two
peasants,
of
the
crownless
king;
she
had
imagined
the
wintry
forest,
she
had
recalled
the
old
Saxon
ghost
legends,
she
had
appreciated
Alfred's
courage
under
