according
to
my
custom,
for
there
was
no
use
in
blaming
severely,
and
high
encomiums
were
rarely
merited.
I
said
nothing
of
Mdlle.
Henri's
exercise,
and,
spectacles
on
nose,
I
endeavoured
to
decipher
in
her
countenance
her
sentiments
at
the
omission.
I
wanted
to
find
out
whether
in
her
existed
a
consciousness
of
her
own
