this
sobering
process
she
became
calm.
I
now
went
on:
"As
to
the
substance
of
your
devoir,
Mdlle.
Henri,
it
has
surprised
me;
I
perused
it
with
pleasure,
because
I
saw
in
it
some
proofs
of
taste
and
fancy.
Taste
and
fancy
are
not
the
highest
gifts
of
the
human
mind,
but
such
as
they
are
you
possess
them
not
probably
in
a
paramount
degree,
but
in
a
degree
beyond
what
the
majority
can
boast.
You
may
then
take
